MALALANE – A couple in their 80s were injured when three men attacked them at their home yesterday. According to provincial police spokesman, Sgt Gerald Sedibe, the incident occurred around 15:00. “Three men wearing balaclavas, overpowered Dave and Colleen Elphick as they arrived home,” he said. Gerhard Coetzer, owner of Securicon Lowveld who responded to the scene along with the SAPS, said that the couple was then tied up after which the suspects ransacked their home. Securicon’s emergency medical service treated the couple for minor cuts and abrasions on the scene. A case of house robbery is being investigated. Sedibe said that no arrest have been made.  Also read: Scuffle leaves two severely injured Questions arise after Van Wijk Street shooting 